config EOM_MSM
	tristate "Eye Opening Monitor (EOM) framework support"
	help
	  This option enables support for the Eye Opening Monitor (EOM) framework,
	  which provides a generic interface for controlling and collecting EOM data
	  from various hardware subsystems. The EOM framework is typically used to
	  monitor signal integrity and eye diagrams in high-speed interfaces.

	  Enable this option if your platform includes hardware that supports EOM
	  and you need to collect or analyze signal quality metrics.


config USB_MSM_EOM
	tristate "MSM USB EOM driver"
	depends on EOM_MSM
	help
	  This option enables the Eye Opening Monitor (EOM) driver for USB PHYs
	  on Qualcomm MSM platforms. It allows monitoring of signal quality and
	  eye diagram characteristics specific to USB interfaces.

	  Enable this option if your MSM-based system uses USB PHYs that support
	  EOM and you need to collect signal integrity data for diagnostics or tuning
